
==============================================================================
@title@   Oligoacetylene and H4 molecules, polarizabilities
==============================================================================
  
  Oligoacetylene molecule in a box, calculated using different methods
  and including an electric field.

  nspin = 1:      LDA, NK0, NK, PZ, HF, PBE0, B3LYP

  The electric field is set to 0.005 Ha-au
  We can then compute the polarizability as  alpha[Ha-au] = dipole[Ha-au] / efield[Ha-au]

            Dipole [e*bohr]      Alpha [Ha-au]
  LDA:          0.166408             33.28

  NK:           0.163608             32.72
  NK0:          0.137097             27.42
  PZ:           0.147117             29.42
  HF:           0.164857             32.97
  PBE0:         0.161690             32.34
  B3LYP:

======================

